org.cloudbus.foggatewaylib.utils

Class MultiMap<K,V>

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.cloudbus.foggatewaylib.utils.MultiMap<K,V>
  • Type Parameters:
    K - type of the keys.
    V - type of the values in the Sets.

    public class MultiMap<K,V>
extends java.lang.Object
    Map that stores for every key a Set of values. The interface of this class is very similar to Map with the only difference that you can't Map.get(Object) a single value but you can only getAll(Object) values stored for the given key. Furthermore, the method findValue(Object) is added.
    Author:
    Riccardo Mancini
    See Also:
    Map, Set

      • put

        @Nullable
public boolean put(@NonNull
                             K key,
                             @NonNull
                             V value)
        Inserts a key-value pair in the MultiMap. If the key was not already present, it is added and a Set containing only the given value is associated with it. If the key was already present, the given value is added to the Set associated with the given key. NB: if the value is already present in the Set associated with the key, this method will do nothing.
        Parameters:
        key - the key to be added.
        value - the value to be added.
        Returns:
        true if the value has been added, false if it was already present in the Set associated with the key.
